postcontent:
Have a pretty good condition Miroku Liberty Chief 38 for sale. Bought it two weeks ago from a guy and not a big fan of it. If you've ever heard of Miroku, you know they make quality firearms.

Gun was made in the early 60's, so it definitely has carry wear.

**Gun ONLY fires efficiently in single action. Previous owner neglected to tell me this when he swore it "fires anything, anywhere with no problems". I'm not going to sell a gun without warning the next owner about the issues it has. Took it to the range and it seems like someone lightened the trigger too much and the DA only fires every third or fourth pull, but single action fires every round without problems.

From what I'm told it just needs a spring made for it since the first one was modified (Can't buy them anywhere because of the hybrid design) and it should function fine.

Aside from the DA problems, the gun is smooth like butter and a very good shooter despite it's age.

Asking 150 obo for it, because honestly I have NO idea what this thing is worth with shotty double action, so I'm just trying to get back what I paid for it. Also open to trades, I like anything that goes boom.

title: For Sale:  Sig P224 9mm DAK New With 13 New Mags & Nickel Slide & Controls Very Nice
location: All Areas in/near Indy, Indianapolis, Indiana
postcontent:
My brother, my dad, and myself all bought one of these at the same time back in late 2013.  We are now disposing of our dad's estate and have a couple of guns to sell.  

This is a really nice P224 in 9mm.  It's the two-tone, with a nickel slide and controls.  It is also a DAK trigger action.  In 2013, these were fairly easy to find.  Today....they are impossible to get new and nearly so used.  Especially if you carry IWB, the height of the P224 makes it very easy to conceal.  It also will accept all P229 9mm mags (old and new.)  

This gun went to the range one time and fired 13 rounds.  It was cleaned, stored, and hasn't moved since.  There isn't even the beginning of a Sig barrel smiley yet (if you follow Sigs, you know what that is.)  It is the same as new.  

Our dad had a total of 5 12-round mags and 3 15-round mags for the gun.  Only one of the 12-round mags has ever been in the gun.  My brother sold his P224 late last year and still has 3 15-round mags and 2 12-round mags, all unused, that didn't sell with his gun.  So, I am selling this with a total of 7 12-round mags and 6 15-round mags.  

The price is $950 firm for everything.  If you do the math, you're not really buying the gun as much as you are stealing it but I just want it sold and done.  This is essentially a NIB P224 with 13 new mags (the mags are selling retail at about $50 per right now.)  I'm not interested in ANY trades or offers.  $950, cash only, and I don't want to split it up; you buy any of it, you buy all of it.  There's a lot of automated scam responses to Armslist ads; mention the gun by name and include your location.  Age 21+ and Indiana DL.  I'll leave this local for a few days and then move it to GunBroker.
